Overview
This application enables users to upload raw text or entire documents, automatically splits them into manageable chunks, and converts each chunk into vector embeddings stored in a robust database. Through a chat interface, users can leverage either GPT-4 or the lighter 4o Mini model to query these chunks contextually, retrieving relevant text snippets and generating comprehensive, context-aware responses.

Primary Use Case: Upload textual content or documents (PDF, plain text, or other supported formats) to create a personalized knowledge base that can be queried with context.
Core Technologies:
Next.js (React-based) for the frontend and server-side rendering.
Node for backend logic and server-side operations.
ShadCN for a cohesive design system and UI components.
Supabase for storing and managing embeddings and metadata.
OpenAI Embedding Model (e.g., text-embedding-ada-002) for vector generation and semantic search.
GPT-4 and 4o Mini for the conversational AI interface.
Architectural Highlights
Document Ingestion and Chunking

Documents are automatically split into chunks to ensure optimal handling of larger inputs.
The chunk size is configurable, maintaining the balance between maximum coverage of context and efficient retrieval times.
Each chunk is tagged with essential metadata (document ID, sequence index, timestamps, etc.).
Embeddings Generation

Chunks are passed through OpenAI’s text-embedding-ada-002 (or a similarly capable model) to produce vector embeddings.
Embeddings, along with metadata, are stored in Supabase, which acts as a vector database for quick similarity-based lookups.
Search and Retrieval

User queries are converted into embeddings using the same embedding model.
A nearest-neighbor search is performed in Supabase to find the most contextually relevant chunks.
Retrieved chunks are bundled and provided as context for GPT-4 or 4o Mini to generate responses.
Conversational Interface

Frontend is powered by Next.js, delivering a smooth user experience with server-side rendering for quick initial page loads.
A simple, intuitive chat layout built with ShadCN provides the user the option to switch between GPT-4 and 4o Mini for cost or performance considerations.
When the user sends a query, the system fetches relevant chunks, appends them as context, and sends the entire prompt to the selected model.
Scalability & Security

Supabase provides a scalable storage option for embeddings and raw chunk data.
Integration with Next.js API routes (or serverless edge functions) ensures the system can be scaled horizontally.
Fine-grained access controls in Supabase secure the user data and guarantee privacy in multi-tenant scenarios.
Detailed Feature Set
Document Upload

Drag & Drop interface or file selection for uploading.
Real-time upload feedback showing progress and supported file types.
Automatic extraction of text from PDFs, Word documents, or plain text files.
Chunking and Metadata

Customizable Chunk Size: The user or system admin can adjust the size (e.g., 500 tokens or 1,000 characters).
Overlap Setting: Optional overlap to preserve context between consecutive chunks.
Metadata Recording: Each chunk is associated with a unique ID, file reference, chunk index, etc.
Embedding and Storage

All processed chunks are passed through the OpenAI embedding model.
Generated vector embeddings are stored in Supabase tables, keyed by unique chunk IDs.
Additional analytics data (upload timestamp, processing time) for performance tracking.
Chat Interface (GPT-4 or 4o Mini)

Model Selection: A toggle or dropdown allows switching between GPT-4 (for higher quality outputs) and 4o Mini (for lower-latency responses).
Real-Time Chat: Messages appear in a classic chat bubble style, with the system’s responses distinguished from user messages.
Contextual Answers: The system retrieves relevant chunks from the database, feeding them into the chosen model as context.
Adaptive Response: The model references the embedded knowledge base, ensuring domain- or document-specific accuracy.
Design & User Experience (ShadCN)

Minimalist Layout: Clean typography, strategic use of whitespace, and subtle color accents for a professional feel.
Responsive Design: The interface is fully responsive, adapting seamlessly to desktops, tablets, and mobile devices.
Progress Indicators: Visual notifications during embedding or retrieval processes to inform users that the system is working.
Error Handling: Clear error states with guided suggestions (e.g., invalid file type, incomplete upload, or model access issues).
Performance Monitoring & Logging

Query History: Stores user queries (with privacy considerations), timestamps, and response times for debugging or analysis.
Embedding Generation Metrics: Keeps track of embedding requests and latencies for cost-management and scaling decisions.
Usage Analytics: Optional integration for insights into popular queries or documents, potentially driving improvements in chunking strategy.
Modular & Extensible

Model Extension: Easy to add further LLMs or embedding services.
Authentication: Works with existing Supabase Auth or other providers (JWT tokens, OAuth, etc.) for secure user sign-ins.
Multi-Tenant Ready: Each user or project can have a dedicated set of embeddings and documents, separated by workspace or team ID.
